==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Middle Dutch]] ''[[kitte]]'' "a wooden vessel made of hooped staves" and [[boodle]], which may come from [[Dutch]] ''[[boedel]]'' "property, estate". [http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=kit]

===Idiom===
'''[[kit]] [[and]] [[caboodle]]'''

# [[everything]] [[entirely]], the whole lot.
#:''When the gathering was over, they packed all the remnants, '''kit and caboodle''', into the truck and drove off.''

